#: ../../../README.md:2
msgid "STDLIB"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../README.md:4
msgid ""
"A reusable standard library for "
"[Bash](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bash_(Unix_shell))."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../README.md:6
msgid "About"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../README.md:8
msgid ""
"This is my small attempt to create a home for the myriad of helper "
"functions we all seem to end up implementing when cobbling together "
"scripting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../README.md:10
msgid ""
"A mocking system, modelled on Python, has also been included to try and "
"simplify the task of testing scripts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../README.md:12
msgid ""
"This won't cover every use case out there, but it does provide a "
"consistent and extendable API that can easily grow.  Pull requests are "
"welcome, as is feedback and ideas."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../README.md:14
msgid ""
"Comprehensive [documentation](https://bash-stdlib.readthedocs.io/) is "
"also available to get you started."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../README.md:16
msgid "Compatibility"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../README.md:18
msgid ""
"Most of the library is intentionally POSIX in nature, which makes me "
"confident that a wide variety of BASH versions are supported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../README.md:20
msgid ""
"It's important to note that STDLIB in its current form requires GNU/Linux"
" binaries to function correctly.  If there is sufficient interest, "
"support for BSD or OSX environments can be added."
msgstr ""

